Our Purpose

Empowering Young Learners
and Building Future Leaders

We are a nonprofit tutoring initiative created by high school students dedicated to helping elementary school children succeed academically. Our mission is to inspire confidence and curiosity in young learners while fostering leadership and community spirit.

By tutoring elementary students, high school volunteers earn valuable community service hours, encouraging personal growth and civic engagement while making a real difference in our community.

About Us

High School Students
Committed to Community

01

Our Story

Founded by students who know what it’s like to struggle, improve, and succeed. We started SFS to close learning gaps with consistent, encouraging support, and to give volunteers a real way to serve.

02

Our Approach

We match each student with a supportive tutor, focus on foundational skills, and celebrate small wins so confidence grows alongside grades.

03

Our Impact

Our tutors gain leadership skills and a sense of accomplishment through service, while elementary students improve their grades and confidence.
